Argued October 30, In the Matter of the Dissolution of the Marriage of SULFFRIDGE, Respondent, and SULFFRIDGE (No. 37878), Appellant. 515 P2d 182 William L. Lasswell, Roseburg, argued, the. cause and filed the brief for appellant. Fred R. Bernau, Roseburg, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief were Bernau & Wilson, Roseburg.

affirmed without opinion November 5, 1973

Before Schwab, Chief Judge, and Langtry and Tanzer, Judges.
